  "category_detail": "<b>Calendar Dates in Japanese (日付 / ひづけ / hizuke)</b><br><br>Japanese calendar dates use the counter <b>日 (にち / nichi)</b>. However, many dates have <b>special and irregular readings</b>, especially from the 1st to the 10th and also the 14th, 20th, and 24th.<br><br><b>Common Irregular Dates</b><br><span class=\"example\">1日</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(ついたち / tsuitachi)</span><br><span class=\"example\">2日</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(ふつか / futsuka)</span><br><span class=\"example\">3日</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(みっか / mikka)</span><br><span class=\"example\">4日</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(よっか / yokka)</span><br><span class=\"example\">5日</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(いつか / itsuka)</span><br><span class=\"example\">6日</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(むいか / muika)</span><br><span class=\"example\">7日</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(なのか / nanoka)</span><br><span class=\"example\">8日</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(ようか / youka)</span><br><span class=\"example\">9日</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(ここのか / kokonoka)</span><br><span class=\"example\">10日</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(とおか / tooka)</span><br><br><b>Other Important Exceptions</b><br><span class=\"example\">14日</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(じゅうよっか / juuyokka)</span><br><span class=\"example\">20日</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(はつか / hatsuka)</span><br><span class=\"example\">24日</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(にじゅうよっか / nijuuyokka)</span><br><br>All other dates generally follow the pattern <b>number + にち (nichi)</b>.",

